		<h2>THE NEXT GENERATION FUND - SUPPORT THE NEXT GENERATION OF ARTISTS, DESIGNERS AND ARCHITECTS</h2><p>Each year thousands of emergent artists, designers and architects apply to study for a world-class education at The Glasgow School of Art.  As one of the UK's leading independent art schools with a long history of producing successful graduates, it is not surprising that we are often students first choice of where to study and one of the most popular art, design and architecture institutions in the country.  </p><p>However, the cost of studying at art school is considerably higher than other degree courses and for many talented students prohibitive, but we believe access to a world-class education in fine art, design and architecture at the GSA should be open to everyone based on talent, ability and potential.  </p><p>Through Scholarships, the GSA can ensure that all students, regardless of their circumstances, can have the opportunity to realise their potential and study for a degree in fine art, design or architecture.</p><p>The School has limited funds available for scholarships.  By making a donation to the Next Generation Scholarship Fund, you will be helping us to expand the available funds to provide future generations of artists, designers and architects the opportunity to study at The Glasgow School of Art.  </p><p>The Next Generation Scholarship Fund will be used to support students in the following ways:</p><ul><li><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=552" target=""><u>Access Scholarships</u></a></li><li><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=551" target=""><u>Research Scholarships</u></a></li><li><a href="/gsa.cfm?pid=550" target=""><u>International Scholarships</u></a></li></ul><p>Since 2002, the GSA has secured from alumni, friends, trusts, foundations and companies over &pound;1.4m towards scholarships.  </p><p>Some of these donations are annual gifts, used each year to provide scholarships, while some has been given in the form of endowments through gifts or legacies, to ensure support in perpetuity.  </p><p>If you would like to support students now and in the future please contact Scott Parsons, Head of Marketing and Development on +44(0) 141 353 4698 or <a href="mailto:marketing@gsa.ac.uk" target="">marketing@gsa.ac.uk</a>.</p>
	

	

	

	

	

	

	
	
	
	
	


	
	







